  "text": "CLSM was performed to detect differences in the localization of the DOX on larvae after 72 hpi with DOX, MMDOX, and Doxil®. The zebrafish transparency during the larval stage and the fluorescent properties of DOX provide advantages for in vivo visualization and could serve as a valuable tool for identifying tissue-specific distribution. DOX could be tracked even when is encapsulated into nanocarriers using fluorescence-based techniques without any other fluorescence labels [CITATION_1] .",
